{
  "stem": "26111.5",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We each had a note from the girls, maybe with a little gift, and, you know, sort of expressing their pleasure in being able to do this and hoping they would-- that we would enjoy this break.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Well, we enjoyed the break-- in heated building, [LAUGHS] after, after-- out of the December and January winds howling outside.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So it was, it was a wonderful, a wonderful gift-- a good mitzvah-- that they did for us, there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And we of course wrote notes back to the girls, secretly hoping that we could maybe make contact with them.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But I just wrote a note.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But with the lady who was the-- oh, I should also add that the, the teachers-- the senior teachers who were heads of houses, boarding schools are divided into houses, and each of them has a housemistress, and she is the boss of that house.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And the housemistresses stayed behind, and the staff stayed behind, to cook for us and to clean and so on.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And the housemistress stayed behind, to look after the whole caboodle.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And the one that-- I guess mostly because I spoke English-- that had our house-- I was made a prefect, because I spoke English.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "So I was the intermediary between the boys and, and the, and the lady-- the, the housemistress.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And we got to know each other very well.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And she turned out to be just a wonderful person, who kept writing to me, sending me presents, throughout my years in, in England, actually.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And who, when I went to London, offered me her house that-- in Dulwich, suburb of London-- to stay in, because I didn't have a place to stay yet, at that time when I left the, the, the-- guardianship, or the-- not the 'guardianship,' the hostel.",
      "word_count": 46
    }
  ],
